review_text:
A Delightful Shopping Experience at Aldi Swanston Street: Unveiling Hidden Gems

Introduction:
Aldi Swanston Street has captured my heart as an outstanding grocery store, and I am thrilled to share my uplifting review. This bustling supermarket offers a delightful shopping experience, complete with exceptional service, a lively atmosphere, captivating catalogue sales, and intriguing little-known facts. Prepare to be amazed as I delve into the various aspects that make Aldi Swanston Street an absolute gem.

Service:
The customer service at Aldi Swanston Street is truly exceptional. The dedicated and friendly staff members are always ready to assist you, creating a warm and welcoming shopping environment. Whether you need help locating a specific item or have questions about a product, the knowledgeable team is readily available to provide assistance. The checkout process is efficient and hassle-free, thanks to the well-trained cashiers who ensure a smooth and swift experience.

Atmosphere:
Upon entering Aldi Swanston Street, you are greeted by a vibrant and inviting atmosphere. The store is thoughtfully laid out, making it easy to navigate and find what you need. The aisles are well-maintained, and the displays are tidy and visually appealing. The lively music playing in the background adds a touch of energy, enhancing the overall shopping experience and putting a spring in your step as you explore the aisles.

Catalogue Sale Descriptions:
Aldi Swanston Street's catalogue sales are a true delight for savvy shoppers. The weekly catalogues showcase an impressive array of discounted products, with descriptions that highlight the fantastic range of savings available. From pantry staples and fresh produce to household essentials and specialty items, the catalogue sales offer enticing deals that will leave you astounded. The detailed descriptions provide valuable information, ensuring you can make well-informed decisions while taking advantage of the incredible savings.

Little Known Facts:
Aldi Swanston Street is not just a place to shop; it also harbors interesting facts and unique features. Here are a few hidden gems about this store:

1. Sustainable Practices: Aldi Swanston Street is committed to sustainability. They actively promote eco-friendly initiatives, such as reducing plastic waste by offering reusable bags and encouraging customers to bring their own. Additionally, they prioritize recycling and energy-efficient store operations, contributing to a greener future.

2. Seasonal Surprises: Aldi Swanston Street loves celebrating the changing seasons and offers exclusive seasonal products to match the festivities. From holiday-themed treats to garden essentials for spring, you can always find something exciting and relevant to the time of year at this store.

3. Award-Winning Offerings: Aldi is renowned for its commitment to providing high-quality products at affordable prices, and Aldi Swanston Street upholds this reputation. Many of their products have received prestigious awards, showcasing their dedication to delivering exceptional value without compromising on quality.

4. Community Engagement: Aldi Swanston Street actively engages with the local community. They support local charities, schools, and events, fostering a sense of unity and making a positive impact on the neighborhood they serve.

Conclusion:
Aldi Swanston Street is a delightful supermarket that excels in every aspect, making it a truly exceptional shopping destination. With outstanding service, a lively atmosphere, captivating catalogue sales, and a host of little-known facts, this store is sure to impress. Whether you're seeking great deals, a welcoming environment, or a unique shopping experience, Aldi Swanston Street is the place to be. Pay a visit to this wonderful store and prepare to be amazed.

review_text:
UPDATE 02/2023: A few months ago this ALDI was renovated so it's unlike any other ALDI I've ever seen.  It now has much more of a market vibe to it and surprisingly for ALDI only has 2 staffed check outs and lots of self serve check outs.  For a person who loves ALDI it pains me to say that the self serve check outs are a big fail.  Without question they are the worst I have ever used, by a country mile.  I feel like I've won Tattslotto if I can get through a check out without needing help.  Twice recently I've got part way through my check out when something's gone wrong so I've had to take all my shopping to a staffed check out.  It's really not up to ALDI's usual standard... in fact quite the opposite and at times almost turns me off shopping there. I've reduced my rating for this store as a result.
----------------------------------------------------------------

I am a massive ALDI fanboy so bear that in mind... This ALDI used to be a bit of a dump and quite small with low stock levels. It's recently been renovated and is now a pleasure to shop at. Much larger, really pleasant in store design, wide product range including booze. I especially like the freezers which are much better designed than regular supermarket freezers.
The only issue I have, which is not Aldi's fault, is that for some weird reason this particular ALDI seems to be a destination for Chinese tour groups. A horde of tourists (who often don't know how to use their indoor voices) will suddenly descend on the shop, blocking the aisles and checkouts.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Firstly, I would like to thank you for the support and staying open during this pandemic.
I have always had a great experience shopping at Aldi but this last time I certainly did not.
I went to Aldi Swanston street, Melbourne to purchase 2 bottles of wine on Saturday 17th of October and the manager Nikita served me at the tills, his service was so poor from the start of how he approached me.
He asked for my ID, which I unfortunately left at home. I told him, I have my AHPRA registration card on me, I‚Äôm a registered pharmacist so I‚Äôm definitely over 25.
He said, ‚Äúif you look younger than 30, I have the right to deny it‚Äù
Mind you, I am 31 years old.
He said no which I respected, he asked to check my bag which I happily opened my bag to show him, he used his hands to check my bag which I am not happy about at all! He is not allowed to touch my own belongings specially during this pandemic.
I ended up leaving the store, went home and grabbed my driver license and came back.
Upon waiting one more time in the queue to purchase these two sad bottles of wine.
He stood up and spoke out loud from across the tills infront of the whole store saying, ‚Äúmate, if you don‚Äôt have your ID, I‚Äôm not selling you alcohol and I won‚Äôt accept an ID on the phone‚Äù
I felt so terribly embarrassed and my heart was racing from nervousness.
I waited in the queue and the gentleman on tills was quite polite and served me.

I left the store feeling absolutely disrespected and embarrassed to the point that I cried.
I really hope this kind of attitude is not because I‚Äôm a person of colour  and I hope this will be taken seriously.

name: ALDI
review_text:
I was injured in a fall at the South Melbourne Aldi store last evening. I slipped on a piece of lettuce leaf lying on the sloping floor that leads to the exit. Not a single member of staff so much as enquired if I was Ok or needed help. I had to literally crawl across the floor to reach a hand rail which I then had to use to drag myself up off the floor. I have bruising and swelling to my right hand, bruising to my right shoulder & severe neck pain.

I am an elderly woman and it's a miracle I didn't break a hip. I'm disgusted with the in-store staff who offered no assistance, showed no concern and left me to humiliatingly crawl across their filthy floor.

I am also disgusted with the processes for making a complaint. There is no way to phone anyone. I have had to email via their website which leaves me with no record of what I said or even any proof that I sent that complaint in. If I do not receive a reply by the end of today I will be contacting relevant authorities and reporting you for safety violations, Leaving waste products on sloping floors is a clear violation of your duty of care. Leaving an injured old woman to crawl around on a floor trying to get herself up without so much as asking if she needs assistance is a clear violation of basic human decency.

name: ALDI
review_text: ALDI has the worst customer service any grocery supermarket store in the country if they do get some Pleasant staff they don't last very long they're not wanted I've been screaming that yelled at threatened simply for asking questions if you ask for help people just walk away and say they're busy and they mostly sell rubbish not food

name: ALDI
review_text: You have to keep a very close eye on dates of meat. Our own mistake but couple of times we bought chicken that goes out of date the same day and it‚Äôs not even discounted

name: ALDI
review_text:
Recently purchased a Westbay jacket. Sleeves to short, waistband to loose and pockets to shallow.
Loose your quality control and you loose the game Aldi.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Freezers were empty last week, this week 70% still empty. There are no bags AT ALL in the fresh produce section (again) to put fresh vegetables and fruits in, so veggies  are touched and exposed to all surfaces including the cashier touching them to scan. This is a hygienic and OHS issue. When i spoke to the Aldi staff, he strugged his shoulders several with the excuse that there is shortage supply of bags.
Who is the store manager in charge and overlooking these matters. Either this Aldi store is badly managed or has staff shortage or staff are just too lazy to re- stock items. South Melbourne Aldi store needs to pick up their game, as outer suburb Aldi stores don't have this issue.

name: ALDI
review_text: Would be nicer if they clean up the place a bit and have more variation

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

Staff were friendly and helpful in helping me move the large object. Only down side was they wouldn‚Äôt hold the item (even with payment) to allow me to wait for a friend to come pick me up. review_text: Aldi good value but if you are parking upstairs where it clearly says 2 hours free. When we came out boom gate wouldn't open. I ended up paying $6 on card. name: ALDI
review_text:
I bought a few groceries here and found the selection really good and the quality exceptional.

Check out the trolley token-- American Aldi needs to step up it's game! (I can't tell if these would work in the states. Here you get your same cart back. In the stores I shop in the states you get the cart of the person on front of you.)

name: ALDI
review_text: Great Aldi. Staff and service are great. Downside is it‚Äôs a smaller Aldi so stock is sometimes limited.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great place. Easy parking. And free parking for 2 hours. Close to city as well as my house in Toorak. Friendly staff ..

name: ALDI
review_text:
As a European living in Melbourne I make regular visits to Aldi...and absolutely love it!

The Aldi supermarkets here look very renewed compared to back home...

Today in the South Melbourne supermarket, however, I had a not so good experience...

I went to Aldi and bought some groceries which I paid for. Then I went out and realised I forgot to buy eggs and some fruit. Went back in and when I went to pay the lady asked me to open up my bags...which I did and I told her that I had just visited Aldi. She asked for a receipt, but I couldn't find it.

I then checked again on the side and felt uncomfortable because I wasn't able to find my ticket. Luckily a kind man calmed me and said I could show my Bank Account on the App instead. Which I eventually did.

I understand the lady was doing her job and procedures count, however, she lacked of empathy. I told her I didn't feel the need to buy the extra groceries and left them at Aldi.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Fruit and veg seem to be going downhill from when it first opened.
But it might be just the day I go in. Maybe I might change my days and see if it's fresher. ü§î

Some products are cheaper in compare to other shops like Coles or Woolworth (depends if they have specials like half price).
I also like the weekly specials, every now and then I can find something cheap and useful.

name: ALDI
review_text: Prices good, not sure about product quality. Service is really bad, never ever anyone to help you.

name: ALDI
review_text: All open on AFL Friday in Melbourne

name: ALDI
review_text: Very good super market sells fresh produce, groceries and many more items required for family. Prices are affordable and friendly customer service.

name: ALDI
review_text:

It's not that ALDI is sub-par - I think it's just that I'm spoilers for choice & as a guy in his early 60's, I could be "becoming" a grumpy old man! üò§

name: ALDI
review_text: Small nice store for shopping, bit messy

name: ALDI
review_text: South Melbourne is my preference over St. Kilda for ease of parking and access. The downside is how at busy times there are often queues with up to 10 people, so be selective with your visit time. The other impressive aspect is value for money and without fail, every cashier checks I've QR signed in.

name: ALDI
review_text: It's easy to find specials

name: ALDI
review_text: Like a Hermit Crab I swap my box as I traverse the store picking up ever more. Always more than was on the list. And at the end I strategise my checking out. I plan out my box stack, mirror it and lay it on the travelator, spaced with intent to so the clerk is slow when I need him to be as I stack the more difficult to place items. I play the game of Aldi hard. And. I. Always. Win. Except last time when I forgot to pack my paw paw lip balm. But I don't think that was my fault.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi is supposed to be cheaper than other supermarkets but when I have compared the price here it is a bit higher for food

name: ALDI
review_text: Big store with everything you need. Good quality and reasonable price. Save a lot of money in comparison to Woolworths and Coles. Much better quality, too. Really enjoy ALDI.

name: ALDI
review_text: It's disappointing after all the effort we have gone to in Victoria that the store manager can't wear a mask properly. What a great example for the staff,  and what little regard displayed for the safety, health and wellbeing of customers and the broader community.

name: ALDI
review_text: What‚Äôs with the bag checking? The way they check your bag is like saying you‚Äôre a criminal until proven otherwise. Will never shop there again!

name: ALDI
review_text:
Extremely rude. Went there today. Waited outside for 45 minutes because of capacity which is totally fine. A worker inside screamed at me in front of everyone who lined up because I apparently ignored the rules of just 6 ppl being inside, I actually just stepped into the office because of a lady who just left. 9 people in the room including a whole family who stayed there for more than an hour but screaming at someone who accedintly stepped in because I haven't recognised ur little tiny miny sign? I never gave one star...  but I just felt ashamed how you treated your customers. Thanks
NO!

name: ALDI
review_text: Well stocked regularly, towards the end of the day of course will be less. My honest favourite part of an Aldi trip is to try pack the bag as things get scanned and fired to you at the same time as paying.

name: ALDI
review_text: It's a good place to buy your basics but try to get to the shops early on weekends as they run out of stock on shelves soon

name: ALDI
review_text: This store is good, but I'm still dirty after a staff member yelled at me for "cutting in line" to enter the shop when I'd already shopped there and was returning my trolley. Did she think I found this trolley outside? I just wanted my $1 coin back... This was a day when there was a line outside to get in.

name: ALDI
review_text:
The only good reason to go here is the friendly staff.

About the products:

Parmigiano: this Aldi sells three different types of Parmesan of the same brand: the triangular shape one, the grated one and the shaved one. You are lucky if you find one of them. It‚Äôll never get restocked.
Speck: I bought it for years, now it‚Äôs not in stock since 2 months.
Remano Extra virgin olive oil: always sold out.

Can‚Äôt rely on this shop for your weekly groceries.

name: ALDI
review_text: We continue to do our weekly food shop here. I find the prices are so much better then Coles or Safeway. The layout of this store is great and there are always weekly specials. This store is located a short walk from South Melbourne market which means that if there is anything else that is needed, we can take a short stroll. There is plenty of parking available at this store, which is free for the first 2 hours.

name: ALDI
review_text: Best for management to communicate to staff how many of the same item a customer can purchase to avoid misinformation, rudeness and a waste of everybody's time. Two stars for the young girl apologising for getting it wrong and opening a new checkout for me. Supermarket employees must be under great duress at the moment, so their managers need to step up. I don't do budget stores and my first visit today reminded me why.

name: ALDI
review_text: Very good products excellent choice of products and responsible prices free parking for 2 yours is a bonus the only fault that they could improve on is they should over a longer hold on large items once you have paid for them in full they should nice you at least 48 hours to arrange pick up at the moment they only give you 1till the next day I have lost many items as I could not organise pick up quick enough that‚Äôs the only thing that I believe was unreasonable as the product is fully payed for surely they could give you some time to arrange transport on big furniture items !

name: ALDI
review_text: Thankyou to the security guard that was on last night. He helped me get my car out of the car park. I would've been screwed otherwise. He was so friendly about it too. Thankyou Sir!

name: ALDI
review_text: A good store to buy groceries, cheap prices and various discounts options. They have various discounts on liquors which is better than Dan Murphy. The staff is not that great though.

name: ALDI
review_text: A nice store, always clean. The checkouts move pretty quickly, the staff open up a register when it starts geteting busy - I've never had to wait too long. The staff are generally friendly, and the shelves are well stocked.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great parking, good location and a well stocked store. The staff are always busy, helpful and nice.

name: ALDI
review_text: Everything at aldi is a dollar cheaper than coles.. So, you're giving coles 40-100 bucks for nothing, every time u go there.

name: ALDI
review_text:
The manager has not the skills needed for his position. His lack of qualification and his bad problem solving resources, in this very risk public health situation, make him a dangerous person, who put in risk his team and the health of the costumers.
If you can go to other store, please do it.

name: ALDI
review_text: Oliver and team offer a genuine and considerate approach to stylish hair for men with wonderful heart and attention to detail.

name: ALDI
review_text: Nice and safe place to go for shopping.but a new rule of parking charges has been imposed

name: ALDI
review_text:
This Aldi store is great for visits if you're in the area. There's on-street parking, albeit quite limited in both quantity and time, but there's plenty of 2-hour parking above Aldi which gives you access to Aldi, and the rest of the local shopping district.

The Aldi itself has a great selection of fresh fruit and vege plus the usual Special Buys promotional items that draw most people into the store on Wed and Sat.

The store is nice and bright and there are plenty of checkouts to get you back on the road.

name: ALDI
review_text: Easy parking, all the usual good food stuff

name: ALDI
review_text: I had a bad experience on the 9th of April at around 2:00. We were served at the register by a lady (i think she might've been the deputy manager??). She was incredibly rude. My partner and I wanted to buy flour and I understand the policy for that is a max of 2 kg per purchase. However, my partner and I don't live together as I live with my family. My aunt who lives with me told me to buy 2 kg of flour and my partner also needed some as well. The lady at the register accused us of abusing the system. We were more than happy to separate the purchase however she continued to insinuate her accusation. Very upset that we didn't have enough flour at home as I live with a lot of people :(

name: ALDI
review_text:
Just another Aldi store that had sold out of lies of stuff; Yes, they're were things I wanted that were missing from the shelves and freezers.

It is what it is though, right...

name: ALDI
review_text: ALDI are consistent and reliable across all locations, and the South Melbourne location is no exception. One great benefit though is the 2 hours free parking - enables you to experience the South Melbourne Market area and some great food outlets.

name: ALDI
review_text: Super quick to get in and out, which is just want you need on a lunchbreak visit. Found everything I wanted very easily, was a bit annoying having someone polishing the floor in the middle of the fresh fruit & veg section tho!

name: ALDI
review_text: I love coming in for the weekly specials. Great that they are keeping more stuff for kids. Excellent prices. Bought Enduroshield when it was $25 and that was exactly half the price as what Bunnings was selling it for!! Good quality food too

name: ALDI
review_text: Very convenient to shop here. Easy parking and up to 2 hours free. Parking can be quite busy on the market days though

name: ALDI
review_text: Great little supermarket with excellent quality fresh produce (vegetables and fruit), as well as friendly staff and good prices.   The special one-off items for sale in the middle of the store often include great products.  E.g. the saucepans and Dutch oven I bought earlier in the year are the best I've owned (despite being 1/10th the price).  I used to shop mainly at Coles or Woolworths in South Melbourne, but Aldi is now my favourite.

name: ALDI
review_text: Terrific Store and much bigger and more variety than my usual ALDI Store

name: ALDI
review_text:
I really, really would hope that ALDI would jump on the online shopping wagon!
As with most people living close to this store we live in apartments that have small car spaces that are not close to the actual apartment. Maybe if ALDI could offer a local delivery service after the shop this would be magic.! .

name: ALDI
review_text: Decent selection, not great. Aldi seems to be getting more and more expensive recently - might as well save the bother of travelling and go to my local coles! Worth going for the special buys and the odd cheaper item. Sadly, no baskets at South Melbourne Aldi so had to buy a trolley coin to shop (who carries change anyway?)

name: ALDI
review_text: Worst staff ever so rude and demanded to see my bag, I refused on principal as I'm not a criminal and don't appreciate  being searched. Let me make you aware of something, plastic bags are banned and as a result most people carry bags, women mostly have handbags, if you search everyone and treat your customers like that no one will shop there. I'd rather go to Coles or Woolworths and be treated with some respect. Will be boycotting you from now on and telling everyone to do the same until I get a formal appologie from the rude staff member and you change you policy

name: ALDI
review_text: Good size store. Easy parking.

name: ALDI
review_text:
No baskets, makes carrying groceries difficult.
Deputy Store Manager (blonde female) is rude, could not do basic maths and I received extremely bad service at checkout.

name: ALDI
review_text: Nice wide aisles. Uncluttered for a smaller outlet. Very clean and easy parking. Ok selection considering the size of the store.

name: ALDI
review_text: Like every other Aldi it's very familiar setup and let's be honest I would assume that most people who go to shop there including myself go obviously for the fact it saves you money,  but it's the fact that they sell everything. It's the surprise factor finding something that you want that's in the price range that you expected that it should be. It's even better when you find it and it's in the reduced price section. Seriously Aldi defies the old notion of going shopping for groceries, and as i said before it's great to have competition. For to   long we the public where told by the big 2 supermarkets that this is your selection and these are the prices you will pay. As much as they would have loved it to still be like that, unfortunately for them they couldn't stop it. We still are considered as a overpriced country and some of the companies who come here come only because of that. Knowing that we'll pay that extra not because we like it but because our elected politicians don't do nothing to change that. Be lets hope there is some company who the people who are running it make that decision to change that perception. Back to that great chain called Aldi don't stop surprising us

name: ALDI
review_text: I really do enjoy going to this store especially since  the refurbishment.. Aldi have a good selection of products.. the one thing I  think Aldi as a chain could improve on is the checkout system they have especially if you  only have a few items

name: ALDI
review_text:
Today I thought I would try this Aldi store after some six months of avoiding it only to be reminded of why that was.
No baskets, services is non existent, if you are to ask for an item that was missing in shelves you are responded to with some kind of hostility.
You are rushed to take items of the register as they have been scanned, the problem is even when you are purchasing a cart bag, they scan other items first and still rush you to take items of the counter. I think it world help if they scanned the bags first to speed up the process. Chances are I will not be here for another 6 months of a yearyear-round

name: ALDI
review_text:
The staff here are alright, it's as good as most aldi stores.
Unfortunately the stock in the centre of the store wasn't the same as other aldis further out from the CBD which have items we wanted.

name: ALDI
review_text:
OK, so its clean and modern but I still struggle with the almost total absence of nationally known brands. I generally choose items based on my perception of brand quality so I'd have to invest time (and purchases) at Aldi to get to know its brands - otherwise its just random selection.
The store doesnt have as big a range as the Woolworths (in the next building) and the carpark above the shop is very small... Was a long wait to get a park there last visit.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great aldi free 2hr parking nice to shope there for great prices as well as seeing what new product promotion sales through the middle tables :)

name: ALDI
review_text:
Great store after the retro-fit. The staff are very helpful.
Too bad that the panic buying/ FOMO fools strip it bare first thing in the morning leaving nothing for those who really need it.

name: ALDI
review_text: The ALDI in South Melbourne don't like the layout as other Aldi  stores it feels a bit of chaotic

name: ALDI
review_text: Other than groceries, few essential items available like tent, bed, quilt, art supplies, sports items etc. But only problem those are not always available. You need to visit frequently and may be you will get whatever you are looking for in a good deal.

name: ALDI
review_text: Stock availability is good, good prices, but there is a surcharge when paying with debit / credit card that has paypass. This store is closing temporarily for renovation from 18th November 2019.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Aplace of mystery. , every member of staff treats like a thief except the security. Mushrooms are cheaper than else where and don't seem to be attached to the cartel agreement or agreements between mushroom producers that keep mushroom prices high in Australia.
Sells knockoffs of euro chocolate brands fairly decent, but a stall the market next door often sells the real deal for cheaper such a Ritter sport.
I visit this supermarket twice monthly.

name: ALDI
review_text: As well as great prices on supermarket goods, this Aldi outlet has good undercover parking (free for first 2 hours) and is close to both York Street Stop 127 on St Kilda tram route no 12 and City Road Stop 126 on tram route no 96.  Also, well done Aldi for giving your workers a 10 percent pay raise during the COVID pandemic as well as installing clear screens at the registers and 1.5 metre social distancing floor markers at the checkouts. I also love the fact that ALDI has battery recycling bins for customers to dispose their used batteries.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great prices but they scan everything too quickly, it‚Äôs just so stressful

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi. You have it all. Organic products. Gluten free pasta. Almond milk and a selection of beers - both own brand and international - that gets me excited. The champagne is so reasonable too and it is really really good. You wld be a fool to shop anywhere else. Oh... and that middle aisle of goodies always has something you need. From UHD TVs to gardening gloves. Love it.

name: ALDI
review_text: Not a bad shop for certain items, a bit disappointed every single one of the ‚Äúspecials‚Äù are made in China items, it‚Äôs time to support Australian businesses rather than sell cheap goods, just my opinion, the average consumer may think differently

name: ALDI
review_text: To be honest, if a supermarket gave up on life, this would be it. Not a fantastic experience for the first timer. They get two stars for the solid phone plan they offer.

name: ALDI
review_text: Very clean üëå I normally shop at the Franklin St Aldi, it was like shopping at the same store everything is in the same location üòÄ

name: ALDI
review_text: I'm an ALDI Holic...always great product range...my favourite Go To Stores on my Aussie travels...this store is central to St Kilda...only difficulty is parking under the store...very tight...but worth the effort if you're in the area...

name: ALDI
review_text: Don't stock all bread and other products, one of the staff was literally banging trays on top of display fridges, surprised she didn't break it. She looked like she was hating her job.

name: ALDI
review_text: When it comes to the price it's awesome but when it comes to availability it's bit disappointing. You will find fruit and veg section empty in evenings. Some times you need to wait in que's too long to get served.

name: ALDI
review_text: A comfortable place to shop here. Well organized and easy to find out items you wanted.

name: ALDI
review_text: Prices cheaper than other major retailers, but run out of stock a lot, and sometimes not enough staff on checkouts.

name: ALDI
review_text: Overcrowded. Don't believe Aldi is cheaper than Woolworths brand. Can't believe they continue to charge a surcharge on credit cards. Greedy

name: ALDI
review_text: Not very large, but you"ll get all your  products you're used to. You might miss out on weekly fun specials though as they don't get a very large stock

name: ALDI
review_text:
Cheapest place to buy your grocery
Different from coles and woolworth

name: ALDI
review_text: Staff are very friendly and helpful. I have always come out of there with everything I need. Nice clean Aldi store.

name: ALDI
review_text: I always enjoy shopping here. Still amazed by how much groceries I can get at such a low price and excellent quality.

name: ALDI
review_text: Good as other stores. The layout was a bit different to what we have in Sydney but the friendly staff was quite helpful.

name: ALDI
review_text: Customer service is terrible at this store every time. Staff are never willing to help and are so rude to customers at checkout. Most of the time only 1 register is open and they scan and throw around your groceries like there's no tomorrow!

name: ALDI
review_text: Next to Dan Murphys and near Woolworths. Both have free parking so great to do shopping at both and compare prices with little effort. Added benefit of being right near the markets. It's my favorite Aldi

name: ALDI
review_text: Good selection of food. Staff are friendly and the queue moves pretty quick, they add someone extra if it gets busy.

name: ALDI
review_text: It ranges from all categories and I am anxiously waiting for the best Doonah's to come back to Aldi

name: ALDI
review_text: Doesn't have the best range but mostly what I want. Prefer to go to South Melbourne Markets first but Aldi is a good place to pick up some decent staples at a good price.

name: ALDI
review_text: This AlDI shop is with reasonable size, that you can get bargains than the nearby Woolworth supermarket. If you want to save 15% or more, shop in ALDI.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Aldi's stores are quite big and usual you can find anything that you want which usually is cheaper than Coles and Woolworths
There's no shopping basket :( just shopping cart

name: ALDI
review_text: Long queue at the checkout on weekends. Not quite acceptable. Need to increase staffing at checkouts

name: ALDI
review_text: They renovated this place late last year and now it is even better. It still a good price, but now they have more diverse offer.

name: ALDI
review_text: Always good at South Melbourne

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI
review_text: Cheap and Good. Period.!

name: ALDI
review_text: Always has things in stock that other stores tend to run out of. Handy free parking upstairs too.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great place for groceries, best time to buy fresh produce is before 5-6 p.m., helpful staff close to CBD, good parking.

name: ALDI
review_text: They seem to have everything i need and even  what i didn't know i needed

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI
review_text:
No social distancing happening here! Shoppers are all over the place.
Aldi staff members - PLEASE control the crowd and social distancing for everyone‚Äôs safety!

name: ALDI
review_text: Good staff and team, calm location and wide parking place.

name: ALDI
review_text: Convenient but longer store hours would be ideal

name: ALDI
review_text: Easy 2 hour parking with number plate recognition. Very convenient in the same building as Dan Murphys

name: ALDI
review_text:
Well stocked, great position next door to Dan Murphy's, across from Woolworths one block from the Markets, choice of eateries
Top shopping district.

name: ALDI
review_text: Really good prices compared to coles and wollies. Also dont forget to check out tgeir weekly specials on aldi website.. They got really good deals often

name: ALDI
review_text: Great for a change. Actually may start visiting the store much more often in the near future.

name: ALDI
review_text: Good produce,catalogue specials brought in weekly,Mostly Friendly staff.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great location, usual Aldi experience, but what really is great is the parking. Clean, convenient and under cover.

name: ALDI
review_text: Is actually good but they need to fix baskets so you can carry your food.

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI
review_text: Parking availablity above Aldi is usually better and quicker than the 2 floors below Woolies across the road

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI

name: ALDI
review_text:
Cheap alternative to main supermarkets.

ALDI HAS SHAKEN UP THE WOOLIES - COLES SUPERMARKET DUOPOLY
Aldi is now well established in Australia and is getting a reputation for the quality of its fresh produce.
This store is on the ground floor of the  new (Aug 2022) Marker residential complex on the corner of Stanley and Spencer Sts in West Melbourne.
The store has a good selection of packaged  and frozen food.
The fruit and vegetables are fresh but not a very big range. Like other Aldi stores there is a long central aisle filled with hardware, cheap electronics, clothing and household goods.
The store has conveyor belt registers so you can place all your purchases on the belt - something lacking in many smaller supermarkets!

name: ALDI
review_text:
Overall, Aldi South Yarra is a useful place for groceries. Many of their products are better value for money than the competition and the store is very conveniently located near public transport and car parking.
The product range is good relative to the bigger supermarkets, as is the quality.
The store underwent major refurbishment in '22 and the layout is more modern. Items are easier to find. It's usually immaculately clean and tidy.
One gripe though is the appalling quality of the self service checkout machines. They're defective as they keep calling errors, requiring a staff member to come along and clear.
Please fix or replace them, Aldi management! Or put more staff on the checkout lanes please. The competition's self service machines are much better than yours.
Regards Charles

Yes, happy to follow the rules and exit the store through open checkouts BUT polish up your customer service and speak to us with respect. Drop the attitude and show a bit of courtesy and respect!! I finally had it this morning (23/8/21 at 8.43am) that's why I'm writing this review. My total was $34.60, instead of giving me back 40 cents and a $10 and $5 note, which is the easiest way, the guy gives me a whole bunch of coins which add up to $5.40 (5 cents, 10 cent, 50 cent, $1, $2, he gave me everything but the 20 cents) and a $5 note. I stopped and counted and was $5 short. They try to confuse you by giving a lot of coins hoping you don't count it. I'm telling you count your change

review_text: Aldi appears to be better supplied than their competition. Prices too do not seem as high as Woolworths' and Coles' in the current period of rising inflation. The real benefit is that one is less likely to come upon LNP voters or Politicians. Aldi has a carefully calibrated supply chain and appears not to be using the current economic challenges as an excuse to raise prices. I bought a steak for $6 as opposed to the Coles version for $9.

review_text:
Not safe to shop here. They let unmasked people and one stood close to me ignoring lines and when I asked him to step back he abused me. Check out girl simply said " stop this both of you"

Would be funny if things weren't so serious. He should not be served at all. I hate wearing mask but hey I do it for the common good.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Aldi had 2 similar special buys.  A fleece sweat top and a fleece hoodie sweat top.  The standard sweat was $9.99 the hoodie $14.99.  It seems the hoodie was sold out because the ticket for the hoodies had been removed, and the last hoodie was placed with the standard ones.

I mistakenly took the hoodie.  I did not realize my mistake until I checked the price on the receipt before I left the store.  I returned to the same checkout to exchange the hoodie for the standard sweat top.  I believe the checkout manager was operating that checkout.

He refused to concede they were different products with different prices, even though my receipt showed I paid $14.99 for the hoodie and not $9.99.  As far as he was concerned, they had the same scan number therefore all he wanted to do was exchange the sweat tops without giving a refund of $5.

What he needed to do was disregard the scan numbers.  View them as different transactions.  He had to do a refund of the returned hoodie as per the receipt of $14.99.  Then do a new sale of $9.99 for the sweat top.

I don't think he comprehended the 'complexity' of the situation as his mind was too focused on scanned prices, rather than the receipt price.

It seems that if someone decided to return a hoodie tomorrow, they will only get $9.99 instead of the $14.99 they paid, because the current scan price is $9.99.   Aldi's does not recognise the amounts paid on their receipts.

No apology from the checkout manager for the inconvenience he caused.

This store was renovated on 7/10/22. It is the same layout as the refurbishment of the CBD store. It looks better but it seems Aldi is going for a disco shopping experience. I want stress free grocery shopping. Due to loud disco music I entered the store relaxed but left stressed because adrenalin was up. Whoever is designing the renovations must be sacked. I will do less shopping at Aldi.

name: ALDI

Wont be going back for  a long time

name: ALDI
review_text:
I'm usually a big Aldi fan, however recent experiences left me questioning where my loyalties lie. I popped down to pick up groceries for a roast (Aldi sell a delicious leg of lamb for a great price), including lamb and veg. After recently moving out, it's become a personal goal of mine to incorporate more greens into my diet, which usually isn‚Äôt a problem. This time was different. Upon entering the store I noticed approximately 60% of the fresh produce was fully depleted, with no roastable greens left.

While I was lucky enough to secure a scotch fillet steak and Asian salad, the experience nonetheless left a bad flavour in my mouth. I cross my fingers this is a once off Aldi.

review_text:
The store itself if fine, but I suggest you shop elsewhere if you require parking.

I had a shocking experience here last night when I dropped in to buy some groceries for dinner.

The Aldi branded signage pointed me to the car park which clearly states that up to 1 hour is free if you spend $15 or more. I spent $50 and asked to have my ticket validated at the register. This all went smoothly, until the car park boom gate exit said it was not validated and parking was $8 for my 20 minute visit.

I returned to the register and was directed to the store manager, who explained he was new and not familiar with parking validation. He said the car park was run by an external company and that there was nothing he could do. He did try to help, and was nice about it, but the signage is either misleading or their validation machine was misused/broken.

I eventually gave in and paid the $8 for my 20 minute visit, but won't be back after that.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Here are a couple of products that Aldi do way better than others. Most commercial icecream manufacturers,  even luxury brands like Connosieur, add water to their products. This is never an ingredient of real or homemade icecream and which makes even more emulsifiers necessary. They also add lots of air which increases the volume ( yes that's part of the reason icecream is sold by volume not weight!) Ever let your icecream melt in the bowl and havewondered why there's so little liquid in the bottom of the bowl? It's because a significant portion of it was air.
So i was particularly excited to find Kapiti icecream a nz favourite brand of mine on sale at Aldi. I checked the ingredient of theno added water! And the taste of the sticky date and spiced caramel variety i tried? Amazing (with real ginger and nutmeg). And when i melted it, the volume remained the same. And a quick price comparison. 1l Connosieur at Coles (full price):$12. 1l Kapiti at Aldi (full price) $7.69. I'm sold. Good on you Aldi, please don't stop selling kapiti, in fact increase the range: 2 is just not enough.
Full disclosure: i have no commercial arrangement with Aldi or Kapiti and no one has requested this review from me. True!

Apparently there's an Aldi website that shows you what does currently have what, but i haven't located it yet. That'd be the next best thing - between home delivery and out of stock: going to a store that actually has the goods you want.

name: ALDI
review_text: Turned away by security at 7.55pm (close at 8) when I just needed nappies. So frustrating.

name: ALDI
review_text: Nice clean store with friendly staff.

name: ALDI
review_text: How long is fruit and veg kept in storage because 3 days after buying the fruit is rotten.

name: ALDI
review_text: The quality of food has gone waaaaay down over the 4+ yrs I've been going to this store. There's absolutely no customer service, in the store or by phone. I've also talked with a number of employees over the past several years who hold or have held a variety of positions at a number of local Melbourne stores; they've all consistently explained they wished they would be treated like $h!t by their leadership because that would be better than how they currently/were treated.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great choice of quality products, great prices, always leave with so much more than on my shopping list !!! My only gripe is the speed of checkout staff....and having to pack shopping myself to keep up :-(

name: ALDI
review_text: It was great shopping on a Wednesday night  because there weren't huge crowds to contend with. We also got street parking right out front of the store so we didn't have to negotiate the columns in the very tight carpark. I was able o check that the stock that I wanted was on hand before making my way down to the store. Happy to shop there on that night. üåÉ üåõ

name: ALDI
review_text: I do my standard weekly shop at this Aldi and love it for value, quality and service. But posting this especially to thank the security card Tim for seeing my phone lying on the street (it fell out of my bag as I got in to my car) and rescuing it. Thanks so much Tim, you are a lifesaver!

name: ALDI
review_text: The staff and the store are great.  The range is good and I will shop there again.  I am writing this long overdue review due to the harassment I experienced while going about my daily private life which everyone should be able to do without random people deciding to harass another customer, a public figure.  I experienced a level of verbal and psychological harassment at that store in 2018 that is hard to even talk about.  It is symptomatic of a global cultural issue where people suddenly think they have a right to say anything awful to anyone.  It was traumatic and damaging.   It should never have happened and it can never happen again.

name: ALDI
review_text: Appreciate easy undercover parking and access to store.  Has all I need from a local ALDI - good prices for staples.

name: ALDI
review_text: Just another ALDI, with all the good and the bad that comes with it.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi is fine, consistent.  Now has doors on the fridges, save on power

name: ALDI
review_text: 21 oct the so called tradies who installed the height bar going into the aldi car park are stupid. and should be  fired.   the support chain holding up the metal height bar is too weak and is dangerous. i told the manager and he took photos.   iphoned the st kilda police last night 9pm 21 oct.   they told me someone else had also hit the height bar   4 hrs before and it was fixed!!.   i then told the police that i had just hit it 40 minutes ago.   the police officer said they would report it as a public hazard  and deal with it.    i do hope aldi will make sure the support chain is replaced properly. after i hit it the weak chain was broken.  if the bar fell because of pook workmanship it would kill someone.  u have been warned.

name: ALDI
review_text: Super clean store. Ample amount of supplies of goods in the past but recently the number of choices are very very limited and you can barely find items. The staffs are okay but I think they should be more bubbly and hold a smile on their face or atleast a presentable look rather than giving a gloomy look to the customers. These are the things the store can certainly work on. I like this store but rated 3 stars because the main ingredients of professionalism in the service industry is missing there at the moment. So to conclude with, more stock of items and proper customer service.

name: ALDI
review_text: To accommodate me through Raphael Kaleb for Disability Access Victoria and Port Melbourne Life Saving Club I had the most spectacular day in the water.   Thank you so much everyone for your efforts, support and care!!  A day I'll remember forever Xx

name: ALDI
review_text: Had to return a faulty item. They were so good about it and gave me a refund on my card straight away. The security guard üíÇ told me to go inside the store and stand in the queue and I would be served in turn. Much better than another time I was in there and a lady with about 20 items to return went up to the cashier from the other side of the checkout, pushed in and got served immediately. I must admit that she was loud and very demanding though. Two other people and I ended up waiting about half an hour while she returned all her items before we were served. If we'd been told what was happening we would probably have gone into another queue.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Went and tried some single malt whisky.
Not a bad drop.
(Please note I wrote single malt whiskey not scotch whisky.) Made in India!

name: ALDI
review_text: The renovation has made a huge change! I love shopping there now. Great produce and meat at great prices. Obviously the range is somewhat limited compared to the really big stores (not a lot of choice when it comes to herbs and spices etc) but the quality is fantastic and the prices even better. Good value for money.

name: ALDI
review_text: Well I went into the St Kilda store yesterday brought a few things got to the checkout and the over zealous cashier asked to check my small bag which I carry for cards and phone and a bottle of water I flatten the bag which every other cashier has excepted but she insisted that I open all the zipped compartments I refused and I walked out.It was akined to asking a woman to open her handbag. I have shopped at this store since it opened and never had this problem. I am elderly and thats why I have a small bag. I will never shop there again.On a separate note I have found the back store  staff very unhelpful  if you need to ask if a product is in they roll their eyes at you.

name: ALDI
review_text: Respect to the full time security guard that's always there! He honestly makes EVERYONE from all walks of life feel comfortably welcome. I wish there were more decent guys like him doing the job. Maybe he should look at training all of the ones from other retailers who are the opposite to what this guy delivers. Thank you

name: ALDI
review_text: Staff are so helpful & friendly, stocks are starting to fill shelves. One good thing the prices have stayed nearly the same, not like woollies & coles going up

name: ALDI
review_text: Self check out okay fool service slow

name: ALDI
review_text: ALDI has great prices, at kilda one needs the shelfs needs to be restocked more often.

name: ALDI
review_text: 8pm close closed doors 7:45pm üëåthank you

name: ALDI
review_text:
A store I can get into and out of in two minutes with a dinner meal. Only been twice but looks solid. Wish they had more 6 packs cause they sell them at goon bag prices but not sure what alc % the one I looked at was, couldn't find on the bottle.

I'm not sure why every third comment complains about having their bags checked. It's just company policy, and the hill that some of you are choosing to die on is absurd. They sell high quality food that's cheaper than Colesworth. How? They pay less in rent, have less staff working and those who do pick up greater responsibilities. I don't know how you can be so entitled to walk into someone else's shop and feel belittled by an employee enforcing company policy.

I'd 100% do bigger shops here but I ride a motorbike and have a tiny backpack so will probably drop in each day to buy dinner. You can substitute like 85% of your Colesworth shopping to Aldi and buy stuff like deli meats elsewhere, albeit the ones here in st Kilda don't even have them. All in all, Aldi reigns supreme in the St kilda suburb

name: ALDI
review_text: Typical of the renovated stores, wide open aisles, lots of choices and many ALDI special buys. Great for pre-made meals.

name: ALDI
review_text: Padestrian access can be improved. Currently - a single point pedestrian entry and exit, via a disabled ramp, which is long and somewhat inconvenience.

name: ALDI
review_text: Low price, mostly off-brand groceries, that represent good value (relative to other supermarkets). It's a mix of their own brands and common brands, depending on the item. There's also an ever changing assortment of odds and ends that you never knew you needed on special.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi understands the fundamentals of good service and customer loyalty. Greet the customer as a human being with eye contact and an authentic smile. Turns out the first impression is with a security person who totally gets that. Hold on to that security company Aldi Balaclava!

name: ALDI
review_text: Cheaper prices and quieter than big 2 supermarkets. Checkout takes a while though as not many staff and no self serve

name: ALDI
review_text: Same as aldi always is, but this one seems to be very well stocked. Can't ever find any carry baskets which is disappointing as I would have liked to buy more than a handful of stuff and never carry change for the trolleys.

name: ALDI
review_text: In the past. There were no faults however of late the service is bad. Never more than two registers open and constantly running out of stock.  Needs improvement badly

name: ALDI
review_text: They run out of the specials by the afternoon or the day after. False advertising as you can't get a raincheck voucher for the special price to use later. Not everyone is OCD about shopping and lining up as soon as the store is open also during daylight savings they should be open longer hours. Hint hint!

name: ALDI
review_text: Well... what can I say about Aldi ? A true bargain and can get some presents to boot. Nicer food, cheep and much better quality, goodbye Safeway especially Coles , over rated. Also Save more is another awesome place to shop for cheap and bulk items. They change there foods from time to time

name: ALDI
review_text: This morning, this store did a great job of handing out tickets to the first people in line that were after the highly-sought Espresso and air drying machines. While a few people at the very back of the line were disappointed because they waited, the system itself worked exactly as it should have. Props to them for getting it right.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi is just a great place. The quality & pricing is great. Plus the staff are highly oganised as soon as the checkout gets busy they immediately put on more staff. Personally this is one of the best managed aldi stores I have ever been too.

name: ALDI
review_text: Far cheaper than the big 2 less choice thankfully so your visits are short. The middle aisle is a lucky dip. Some of their meats are bland . The noise levels are acceptable. Not the overall range of the duopoly but you learn to adapt.

name: ALDI
review_text: Unfriendly service and always need to check your receipts. Staff don‚Äôt bother to ask what a vegetable product might be so like to overcharge/choose what type/brand of vegetables they want to put your produce through as. End up paying more because they charge the top end product you haven‚Äôt purchased!

name: ALDI
review_text: Plenty of easy parking. Provision of hand sanitiser and trolley wipes. Shelves well stocked, some of my usual products seem to be out of stock. Fresh mac'n'cheese and frozen berries. Middle aisle is uninspiring at the moment. The queues for the tills were fast-moving and the staff member was cheerful. Full trolley $275. Better than Coles.

name: ALDI
review_text: Checkouts are frequently full with long queues - staff have been stocking shelves when really needed on registers. Do not go at peak times

name: ALDI
review_text: This is a straight forward Aldi. The stairs to get in are weird, you kind of have to get around a little gate. There is a ramp though! There‚Äôs a little alcohol section. It‚Äôs fine? Idk. Usually everything is clean and neat.

name: ALDI
review_text: The staff here are very friendly and the store layout is convenient. I can't do my whole weekly shop here as a vegetarian, although there are still some good veggie options and ingredients.

name: ALDI
review_text: Your alcohol policy is quite hysterically baffling. I came in with my 31 year old wife who didn‚Äôt have a drivers license with her. Of course it was a compliment for her to be thought of as under 18, however I most definitely did not look under 18 and was carrying my drivers license with me. Staff refused to serve me. I dropped the shopping in the car, along with my wife and popped back into the store to finish buying the wines, and still the staff refused to serve me. To be frank; I‚Äôm not sure if I need to wait 24 hours to return again or what.. but I‚Äôm still confused, as was every other patron in there that witnessed the events unfold. It‚Äôs a pity, because I do love Aldi, however I must admit, your staff are a little arrogant for my liking. Kills me to have to give a 2 star as I love the brand, but sorry it just had to be done ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§î

name: ALDI
review_text: Super friendly staff when checkout! Don't worry about ques because the cashier's are so fast and get through people really quickly. For an Aldi, very well run. Absolutely no hassle except stock availability :I

name: ALDI
review_text: Self checkout is great. All the usual items in a great modern environment

name: ALDI
review_text: I only wanted lemon drink soft drinks & milk. But I walked out saving $2:??!! So I'll leave my soft drinks for Aldi's. ImpressedüòÖ

name: ALDI
review_text: The Aldi staff honestly think they‚Äôre manning the gates of heaven. Security guards are very friendly. I‚Äôm always more than happy to comply with bag searching, however if you don‚Äôt buy anything and attempt to leave the store, you‚Äôll be asked to show your bag to 4 different staff members who‚Äôll practically chase you out the door and humiliate you in front of the entire store despite having not done anything wrong and being compliant. They also have refused to serve us alcohol despite being 25-28 because our licence wasn‚Äôt Australian? You can‚Äôt enter Australia on a visa if you aren‚Äôt 18. We attempt to show them credit cards, but they don‚Äôt budge. There is nowhere else that expects you to carry your passport around at 28 years old. I understand places have rules but shopping in Aldi has been made so uncomfortable. The European aldi‚Äôs aren‚Äôt like this either.

name: ALDI
review_text: Price is easily superior to Coles and Woolworths. Great parking at side of the building. But the layout, low stock often or missing, freshness of fruit/veggies and staff friendliness is pushing the rating down.  Overall, not bad with room for improvement.

name: ALDI
review_text: Staff members so good ,items at cheaper price, love the Nutcracker and choceur ...

name: ALDI
review_text: We love Aldi, good prices and you can find everything you need. Friendly staff

name: ALDI
review_text: Generally speaking it's a good one.  Sometimes the number of things that are going to be in great demand , ie catalogue specials , haven't  been anticipated for & so are out of stock before you can get there , even on the day that they are advertised!! Maybe it would be good if you could  get more stock or have things put on hold . Not every one can be there at 8.30 in the morning !

name: ALDI
review_text:
St Kilda Aldi had a refurb at the start of the year so now it‚Äôs great. Generally a great selection food and stock levels are good.
Don‚Äôt bother on a Sunday arvo as it‚Äôs stupidly busy. But to their credit they try and open as many registers as they can.
Parking can be an issue sometimes but I generally get a park every time.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Cheap but not much variety
Still good to go

name: ALDI
review_text: Be sure not to be served by the elderly lady on the checkouts... Literally throws your groceries at you, then when you ask her about it she blames management due to her being timed on her lack of service..

name: ALDI
review_text: The new shop lay-out at St Kilda Aldi looks fantastic, compared to what it was like before it now feels and looks much better. I've just taken one star off though becaieeI believe the staff could be a little friendlier. Don't get me wrong no one has ever been outright rude or anything like that, it's just as a customer there's been a few times where I've felt tolerated rather than welcome. Still a great place to shop though and you know I'll definitely be back again and again.

name: ALDI
review_text: We all know aldi is cheap and always busy. Huge discount on Wednesday and Saturday.

name: ALDI
review_text: This is a typical Aldi store with great prices on supermarket goods including produce, meat & dairy. The weekly specials (Wednesday and Saturday) are also great! The major problem with this particular Aldi outlet is the parking. There is reasonable parking but it is somewhat limited  which can be problematic on busy shopping days.

name: ALDI
review_text: This ALDI is great - it's just been done up, has lots of fresh food at great prices, decent size and so far has had a good number of tills open with nice staff manning them. I'm very impressed and intend to make this my regular supermarket now.

name: ALDI
review_text: Self check out at Aldi!! Welcome to the future

name: ALDI
review_text: It's cheap and convenient like most ALDIs. Not always that clean and near closing time things can get quite low on stock. Doesn't have the biggest range but fills the gap between convenience store and supermarkets nicely.

name: ALDI
review_text: The customer service along with the prices are exceptional. Staff are always very helpful. Of particular note would like to thank Store Manager Jason for going above and beyond and tracking down a new release product. He contacted other stores then called me the following day with the good news. This service you would never find at other major supermarkets. A very happy customer. Thank you Jason!

name: ALDI
review_text: apart from Moe and the store manager the inkerman store staff are among the rudest, discourteous and unhelpful bunch of people i have every encountered.  They refuse to listen to requests to slow down when checking out so one can pack.  they refuse to listen to requests for help, they simply turn away, hide from or brush off customers to avoid providing service. i get its a great place to work except for the customers, but folks, rudeness has become your culture.

name: ALDI
review_text: Experienced racism at the store not once but twice. Firstly just trying to ask a question I was over looked. Second time out the number of shoppers, I was hand picked for bag search. I cut my ties with Aldi today.

name: ALDI
review_text: I love Aldi, perhaps a little too much according to my kids and I have been to lots of Aldi's across Australia. There is something about St Kilda Adi that doesn't sit well. The layout is different and they dont seem to carry everything that other Aldi's do.

name: ALDI
review_text: The staff at the St Kilda ALDI are all lovely. It can get pretty busy there, no matter what time of the day you go. They also never seem to have the specials !!! But otherwise ALDI for the win every time when it comes to prices !

name: ALDI
review_text: Great store well stocked and organised.Continuously filling of shelves and a changing array of specials and goodies makes it a very interesting shop. Look out for the parking times in the street as it becomes a clearway and being tourists we were stung for a $159 parking fine for 15min shopping spree. We did not know and coming from Rural area in Tas, clearway are unheard of. Sort of puts a dampner on things..... so Beware.

name: ALDI
review_text:
decent enough Aldi store with the usual groceries, European food products, and of course the "random" non-food products every week.

you have to pay for bags at the checkout, they don't provide baskets to shop, and the trolleys need a coin to take one, which is ridiculous.

name: ALDI
review_text: Cheapest grocery store.  A great selection of fruit and vegetables as well as discounted meat for quick cooking. Very friendly staff here and was helpful to help me find black pepper. If you live near Habitat hq, it is the best option for you to do groceries.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Fell for the usual ALDI special buy trap today :( - This time for a Heat Pump clothes dryer. Spent half an hour in the queue outside the store before opening - they only had 4 in stock to start with - which sold out immediately.

This is not the first time this has happened - I guess I should have learned my lesson by now - It looks like Aldi will never become a store worth bothering with.

This time we decided to try elsewhere - Found a slightly better product on-line - ended up paying $200 more - but at least this was with free delivery and without the huge hassle of dealing with Aldi and their hopeless stock management.

name: ALDI
review_text: Excellent prices and products, particularly this place, has been renewed, and now it is more complete and simple. The meat section is highly recommended for its prices as well as the alcohol. The attention to the public is frankly great

name: ALDI
review_text: Great prices but not the biggest variety. However, that's understandable since the ones excluded are mostly premium brands.

name: ALDI
review_text: Really good prices, good quality. A LOT of AUSTRALIAN made products. I'll be going back next week v

name: ALDI
review_text: Always friendly staff, typical Aldi variety and the weekly specials often have some great goodies. Heaps cheaper than traditional Aussie supermarkets. The recent reno has been a good change. And Aldi is the only supermarket to take back batteries!!!

name: ALDI
review_text: Always a bit busy but great for buying cheap items that are great in quality. I came here to stock up on snacks for a house party. You'll always find whatever you're looking for.

name: ALDI
review_text: I think it's a great Aldi store. The staff work really hard as it's a busy store, so yes sometimes it can be a little messy or the stock can be low (Aldi is delivered every day and has very little stock, reason why prices are low) but even when they are busy like crazy they will always go and look for something if you ask. I find the staff great and I shop there most of the days. Well done to all!

name: ALDI
review_text:
There is a great variety of shopping goods here that are priced competitively. For those unfamiliar to the ALDI experience, many of the goods are still in their factory packed boxes, so there isn't proper shelving perse. You will also come across a lot of unfamiliar, international brands of packaged foods. But don't fret, they all mostly taste amazing still and priced greatly.

Been shopping at ALDI for a while and I can see why travellers and backpackers love to shop here. Cheap, easy, efficient. Lines go lightning quick so be prepared to bag your own goods, use the dividers at the checkout conveyor belt appropriately and have your payment options sorted for the optimal service delivery for you and all waiting.

This has been one of the cleaner, well kept ALDI's I have visited with lovely staff at the checkouts too. Highly recommended for most of your shopping needs.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great prices.. I have been buying frozen pizza 3.70 cooks in 11 minutes reasonable amount of topping and tastes great .. Store is not very clean and always busy at the checkout and can be long waits..

name: ALDI
review_text: You guys need to make your staff some signs for the Chinese tourists that come through on Friday nights, it's very frustrating for other customers. Something like 'if you want a bag you must pay 15c' it will make the process easier for everyone.

name: ALDI
review_text: Quick a s Very Efficient Shopping.

name: ALDI
review_text: Efficient, usually enough counters open. Staff stacking shelves are occasionally uppity and a tad pushy but only a minor gripe  as I'm usually well served and understand what it's like to work in retail.

name: ALDI
review_text: A great place to shop for inexpensive produce and decent products at reasonable prices. Although Aldi doesn't have the widest range of products, you'll find most of the basics at a lower price than Coles and Woolies. Because this particular store isn't very big or popular, you'll find the weekly/seasonal products here don't run out as quickly - except when in comes to anything Dyson.

name: ALDI
review_text: Produce was woeful compared to my local stores in a different state. I wasn't expecting to have to pick through the apples so much. Out of stock of most green leafy bags.

name: ALDI
review_text:
Not many know of this but the fruits and veggies you can get at an ALDI is far better quality than any other supermarket.
Apart from that, you do get a lot of stuff from other uncommon brands which you wouldn't find at a Woolies or Coles and vice versa.

name: ALDI
review_text: Big standard ALDI. It does have a good under cover carpark, and the standard understaffing of checkouts entailing longer than optimum wait times. Also insufficient space for packing

name: ALDI
review_text: Have to stand there and wait ages because they dont have self serves like Coles and Woolies and two checkouts werent in use. Then she asked to look in my bag. Do I look like a thief? Its been years since anybody at Coles or Woolies ever asked this. Things are the same price as Coles and Woolies but the shopping experience is much worse.

name: ALDI
review_text: Very convenient, so close to home, not that close but 10 minutes driving is a peanut, i love the chilli corn canne, but always run out, its so delicious, prise is very reasonable, i got duck fat with affordable price!! Such lucky girl i am.

name: ALDI
review_text: Waited a long time for them to sort out registers. No trolleys available on arrival. Very busy today. Value for money is still there though.

name: ALDI
review_text: Always fun going to Aldi and discover what fun/useful goodies they have in the sakes tables. I got a chest of drawers for $89.99.  Let's see if i manage to ensemble it together ü§£

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi is the best grocery store in Australia.Good price(compared to other supermarkets,the foods are distinctly cheaper),good service,and lots of choice.But its distribution is limited though,compared to coles,woolworths which are can be found in everywhere(but foods are not as good as aldi's).Even coles is close to my home,I keep going to aldi which is really far but worth.Hope in the future,it can be found in every where.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi continues to get better and better. This particular Aldi is accessible, has a good (but not huge) range and is very well priced in their offerings.

name: ALDI
review_text: It's the only supermarket in the town where you need to keep showing your bag inside. You lose time and the economy is not so great,  are cents of difference from other supermarkets. I've spoken several times why they do not put more cameras or security?  I will not go any more until They change this policy.

name: ALDI
review_text: I do my big shop every week at ALDI St.Kilda...I LOVE THAT i KNOW WHERE EVRYTHING IS LOCATED...AND THERE IS LIMITED CHOICE, SO NO NEED TO DECIDE...!! The Service is Great and Quality  of everything is really good.

name: ALDI
review_text: Great location and always well stocked. I wish some of the older less tech savvy folks just paid with cash. You might as well give them a rubix cube instead of an EFPOS machine ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

name: ALDI
review_text: So called fresh fruit and vegetables are not fresh, many vinegar flies and rotting items. Seen many times, not just once. All other items are great, especially the whole frozen Barramundi.

name: ALDI
review_text: Probably the best groceries available but still, its good as a backup option after Coles and Woolies but still the prices are less compared to the other two and so is the quality ,but fresh supplies amd fruits and veggies available all time

name: ALDI
review_text: It's my local Aldi. I like Little Birdwood red. Very nice. And I worked in vineyards and wineries in WA. Margaret River. This smooth, full bodied red, no acid or tanins, is a very nice drop. As is the Sparkling Moscato. Which is unavailable at present. Love checking out the stuff in the middle isle.

name: ALDI
review_text: Very polite & helpful staff & always very neat & clean. Great variety of produce & fresh. Really awsome staff!! One of the best stores. Well done to management & staff at Aldi's St Kilda.‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§‚ù§

name: ALDI
review_text: New isle layout and stock display is an impovement on the previous design.... BUT this is at the expense of the check out area. Getting to the registers is a disaster!! No room for trollies. Customers are " jammed up" like cattle against each other. They obviousely have no consideration for their customers. Will not return.

name: ALDI
review_text: Good prices on every day grocery items and many unusual buys that you won't find in any other supermarket.

name: ALDI
review_text: Love Aldi and have found other stores to be pretty friendly, but it's a shame that this is my local one. They are consistently rude/disinterested. Might start making the effort to go to Prahran instead.

name: ALDI
review_text: Aldi is great value, we buy quality products that are similar to Coles and Woolworths but almost always cheaper. The staff are friendly and parking is always easy. I love that Aldi is in the market place. It's brought Coles and Woolworths prices down but it still way cheaper. Go Aldi!

name: ALDI
review_text: Located on a peaceful street unlike other stores. They have wheelchair accessible entrance. And as usual great place for grocery shopping.

name: ALDI
review_text: I have just seen a posting on the Elwood 3184 website saying that the St Kilda, Inkerman St, security guard prevented the stealing of a bike chained up outside the store. I am sure this is not in his list of duties and just want to thank this security person so much for coming to the aid of a local who (presumably) was unaware that their bike had someone trying to steal it - this guard needs to be made employee of the week

name: ALDI
review_text: Who doesn't love a bargain? Aldi has got the goods!

name: ALDI
review_text: As an aldi, it's not full service, but the savings on organic produce are phenomenal. Great compared to other stores in the area, though it lacks the selection of more expensive grocery stores.

name: ALDI
review_text: Produce reasonably fresh and priced. Placed our goods on the conveyor, and the Aldi employee just walked without scanning our goods. What the? We won't be back

name: ALDI
review_text: Small but convenient store with under cover indoor parking and very good access. Recently renovated and looks sensational inside. Feels much bigger now.

name: ALDI
review_text: One of the worst Aldi stores I've been to. The store is always consistently messy, stock levels of popular items are often low and the whole decor of the store just feels very low rent.

name: ALDI
review_text:

name: ALDI
review_text: ALDI supermarkets have made a massive splash since entering the Australian supermarket business a few years ago. I now do most of my shopping there and only venture to the other supermarkets for products they don't stock. They don't have the name brands of the others but the quality is just as good and the prices are much better. When you talk to people about ALDI some like it and some don't, some will say they love their ALDI. Have you ever heard anyone say they love Coles or Safeway?

I find the layout easier to navigate than most M-L size ALDI, it's a simple grid & east to scan each aisle for essentials.
Superfast service at checkout for busy shoppers.
Last visit I felt faint while checking out &  the staff member looked over to see all OK for me at packing bench before leaving his post.
Cheers ALDI Abbotsford.

name: ALDI
review_text:
I went shopping there around 7pm on Feb 11th. I'm not impressed with they way your staff Alex treating customers differently. The guy before me and the lady after me are both Caucasian. Alex was very kind and friendly to them. He greeted the guy before me warmly and they just chitchat, that guy was so involved with the conversation that he had to stay there a bit longer to put things in bag. Initially I thought they must be good mates. Then when it came to my turn, Alex just pushed my shopping items to the further end that I had to walk around the cashier to be able to put them in bag. In between he dropped one of my shopping item, but said nothing. The whole time he was just keeping a flat face, not coversation not even a hello or hi. Then he turned to the lady behind me and became nice and friendly again. Why? Is that because I've got Asian face?
I'm not expecting to be treated like an VIP, but such behaviour and attitude are simply unpleasant and unprofessional. Aldi, do something for a change!!!

name: ALDI

name: ALDI
review_text: On 21st May I went shopping with family, everything was good until we went to check out. I had gotten my self some alcohol along with our other weekly grocery needs, but the lady at the check out wouldn't sell it to us because she saw my daughter and thought she was underage so my daughter showed her student is which had her date of birth on it but she didn't except it and only asked for her passport. So in the end she took away the alcohol that I was going to buy for myself. This is a family shopping centre so if the parents want to buy alcohol for themselves do the kids that go with them have to be over 18 so they could buy it? My daughter is over 18 years old, but she didn't even touch the bottles and they still wouldn't sell it to us. I've been going to other Aldis since she was young and have always gotten alcohol and there was no problem until I met that lady. It was bad customer service!

name: ALDI
review_text: Always take the time to have a look at the Aldi weekly specials, often find a real bargain from things like power tools to tech gadgets, LCD t.v's with specs that match the big brands, even camping equipment and motorcycle gear, different specials on hand every week, a good tip is if you find something you want it's best to get to your local Aldi early the day the item is offered as often because of the reasonable prices their specials usually sell out fast. Grocery varieties are good as well on par with other named brands you find in other supermarkets, fresh produce and even wine and alchohol. Staff at Aldi stores I've found are always friendly and helpful, recommend taking a stroll through an Aldi if you haven't already to see the offerings they have, worth a look with prices to match on most products.
